rules.fullText:
{{BOLD}}<GG8>{{/BOLD}} {{BOLD}}Keep your Robots together.{{/BOLD}} {{LINK:#robot}}Robots{{/LINK}} may not intentionally detach parts during the {{LINK:#match}}Match{{/LINK}} or leave mechanisms on the Field.
 Note: Parts which become detached unintentionally are a {{LINK:#minorviolation}}Minor Violation{{/LINK}}, are no longer considered “part of a {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}},” and should be ignored for the purpose of any rules which involve {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} contact or location (e.g., Scoring) or {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} size.

{{VIOLATION_NOTES}}Violation Notes: {{LINK:#majorviolation}}Major Violations{{/LINK}} of this rule should be rare, as {{LINK:#robot}}Robots{{/LINK}} should never be designed to intentionally violate it. {{LINK:#minorviolation}}Minor Violations{{/LINK}} are usually due to {{LINK:#robot}}Robots{{/LINK}} being damaged during gameplay, such as a wheel falling off.{{/VIOLATION_NOTES}}

