rules.fullText:
{{BOLD}}<GG13>{{/BOLD}} {{BOLD}}All rules still apply in the Autonomous Period{{/BOLD}}. {{LINK:#team}}Teams{{/LINK}} are responsible for the actions of their {{LINK:#robot}}Robots{{/LINK}} at all times, including during the {{LINK:#autonomousperiod}}Autonomous Period{{/LINK}}. Any {{LINK:#violation}}Violations{{/LINK}}, Major or Minor, committed during the {{LINK:#autonomousperiod}}Autonomous Period{{/LINK}} will result in the {{LINK:#autonomousbonus}}Autonomous Bonus{{/LINK}} being automatically awarded to the opposing {{LINK:#alliance}}Alliance{{/LINK}} and make the violating {{LINK:#team}}Team’s{{/LINK}} {{LINK:#alliance}}Alliance{{/LINK}} ineligible for the {{LINK:#autonomouswinpoint}}Autonomous Win Point{{/LINK}}.
 If both {{LINK:#alliance}}Alliances{{/LINK}} commit {{LINK:#violation}}Violations{{/LINK}} during the {{LINK:#autonomousperiod}}Autonomous Period{{/LINK}}, then no {{LINK:#autonomousbonus}}Autonomous Bonus{{/LINK}} will be awarded.

{{VIOLATION_NOTES}}Violation Note: In general, {{LINK:#minorviolation}}Minor Violations{{/LINK}} of SG rules that occur during the {{LINK:#autonomousperiod}}Autonomous Period{{/LINK}} should only affect the outcome of the {{LINK:#autonomousperiod}}Autonomous Period{{/LINK}} (i.e., the {{LINK:#alliance}}Alliance{{/LINK}} can’t win the {{LINK:#autonomousbonus}}Autonomous Bonus{{/LINK}} or earn an {{LINK:#autonomouswinpoint}}Autonomous Win Point{{/LINK}}) and should not be considered when determining whether a {{LINK:#violation}}Violation{{/LINK}} has been repeated during the event.{{/VIOLATION_NOTES}}

{{VIOLATION_NOTES}}If a {{LINK:#headreferee}}Head Referee{{/LINK}} determines that a {{LINK:#violation}}Violation{{/LINK}} of an SG or GG rule during the {{LINK:#autonomousperiod}}Autonomous Period{{/LINK}} was intentional/strategic rather than accidental/situational, it should be recorded as a Minor or {{LINK:#majorviolation}}Major Violation{{/LINK}} and considered when determining whether a {{LINK:#violation}}Violation{{/LINK}} has been repeated during the event.{{/VIOLATION_NOTES}}

