rules.fullText:
{{BOLD}}<GG18>{{/BOLD}} {{BOLD}}Use Blocks to play the game.{{/BOLD}} {{LINK:#block}}Blocks{{/LINK}} may not be used to accomplish actions that would be otherwise illegal if they were attempted by {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} mechanisms. If a rule is Violated through the use of a {{LINK:#block}}Block{{/LINK}} instead of a {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} mechanism, it should be evaluated as though the rule in question had been Violated by a {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} mechanism. Examples include, but are not limited to:

• Interfering with an opponent’s Autonomous routine per <SG7>
• Using a {{LINK:#block}}Block{{/LINK}} to intentionally tip or {{LINK:#entangle}}Entangle{{/LINK}} an opponent {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}}
{{CALLOUT}} The intent of this rule is to prohibit {{LINK:#team}}Teams{{/LINK}} from using {{LINK:#block}}Blocks{{/LINK}} as “gloves” to loophole any rule that states “a {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} may not [do some action].” This rule is not intended to be taken in its most extreme literal interpretation, where any interaction between an {{LINK:#block}}Block{{/LINK}} and a {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} needs to be scrutinized with the same intensity as if it were a {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}}.
 {{/CALLOUT}}

