rules.fullText:
{{BOLD}}<SG5>{{/BOLD}} {{BOLD}}Each Robot gets one Block as a Preload.{{/BOLD}} Prior to the start of each {{LINK:#match}}Match{{/LINK}}, each Preload must be placed such that it meets all of the following criteria:

a. Contacting one {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} of the same {{LINK:#alliance}}Alliance{{/LINK}} color as the Preload.
b. Not contacting the same {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} as another Preload.
c. Not contacting or within the volume of a {{LINK:#goal}}Goal{{/LINK}} or {{LINK:#loader}}Loader{{/LINK}}.
{{VIOLATION_NOTES}}Note: If a {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} is not present for their {{LINK:#match}}Match{{/LINK}}, then that {{LINK:#robot}}Robot’s{{/LINK}} Preload may be used as a {{LINK:#matchload}}Match Load{{/LINK}} in accordance with <SG9>.{{/VIOLATION_NOTES}}

{{VIOLATION_NOTES}}Violation Notes: See <SG1>.{{/VIOLATION_NOTES}}

