rules.fullText:
{{BOLD}}<R5>{{/BOLD}} {{BOLD}} Robots must fit within an 18” x 18” x 18” volume.{{/BOLD}}

a. Compliance with this rule may be checked using the {{LINK:https://www.vexrobotics.com/276-5942.html}}official VEX Robotics On-Field Robot Expansion Sizing Tool{{/LINK}}.
b. {{LINK:#eventpartner}}Event Partners{{/LINK}} may construct and/or provide any sizing tool that measures the correct dimensions.
c. Any restraints used to maintain starting size (i.e., zip ties, rubber bands, etc.) must remain attached to the {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} for the duration of the {{LINK:#match}}Match{{/LINK}}, per <GG8>.
d. For the purposes of this rule, it can be assumed that {{LINK:#robot}}Robots{{/LINK}} will be inspected and begin each {{LINK:#match}}Match{{/LINK}} on a flat standard foam field tile.
{{CALLOUT}} The official sizing tool is intentionally manufactured with a slightly oversized tolerance. Therefore, any contact with the sizing tool (i.e., a “paper test”) while being measured should be considered a clear indication that a {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} is outside of the permitted size. This tolerance also provides a slight “leeway” for minor protrusions, such as screw heads or zip ties.
 Other tools, such as custom sizing boxes or the legacy non-expanding VEX Sizing Tool (276-2086), may be used for informal checks. However, in the event of a conflict or “close call,” a check with the official On-Field {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} Expansion Sizing Tool takes precedence.
 {{/CALLOUT}}


{{CALLOUT}} This rule is applied differently for VEX U. See Rule <VUR1>.
 {{/CALLOUT}}

