rules.fullText:
{{BOLD}}<R15>{{/BOLD}} {{BOLD}}Give the radio some space.{{/BOLD}} The V5 Radio must be mounted such that no metal surrounds the radio symbol on the V5 Radio.

{{CALLOUT}} It is fine to loosely encapsulate the V5 Radio within {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} structure. The intent of this rule is to minimize radio connection issues by minimizing obstructions between VEXnet devices. Burying a radio deep within a {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} may result in {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} communication issues. It is also recommended that the LEDs on the radio be visible to aid in troubleshooting.
 {{/CALLOUT}}

