rules.fullText:
{{BOLD}}<T11>{{/BOLD}} {{BOLD}}Each Team will have at least six Qualification Matches.{{/BOLD}}

a. When in a tournament, the tournament must have a minimum of six (6) {{LINK:#qualificationmatch}}Qualification Matches{{/LINK}} per Team. The suggested number of {{LINK:#qualificationmatch}}Qualification Matches{{/LINK}} per Team for a standard tournament is eight (8) and up to ten (10) for a championship event.
b. When in a league, there must be at least three (3) league ranking sessions, with at least one (1) week between sessions. Each session must have a minimum of two (2) {{LINK:#qualificationmatch}}Qualification Matches{{/LINK}} per Team. The suggested number of {{LINK:#qualificationmatch}}Qualification Matches{{/LINK}} per Team for a standard league ranking session is four (4). Leagues will have a championship session where elimination rounds will be played. {{LINK:#eventpartner}}Event Partners{{/LINK}} may choose to have {{LINK:#qualificationmatch}}Qualification Matches{{/LINK}} as part of their championship session.

