rules.fullText:
{{BOLD}}<VAIG3>{{/BOLD}} {{BOLD}}Teams are responsible for the actions of their Robots.{{/BOLD}} Just as V5RC and VURC {{LINK:#team}}Teams{{/LINK}} are responsible for the actions of their {{LINK:#robot}}Robots{{/LINK}} during the {{LINK:#autonomousperiod}}Autonomous Period{{/LINK}}, VAIRC {{LINK:#team}}Teams{{/LINK}} are responsible for the actions of their {{LINK:#robot}}Robots{{/LINK}} throughout the entirety of a VAIRC {{LINK:#match}}Match{{/LINK}}. Excessive or egregious {{LINK:#violation}}Violations{{/LINK}} of the following rules may result in a {{LINK:#violation}}Major Violation{{/LINK}} / {{LINK:#disqualification}}Disqualification{{/LINK}}, as well as the {{LINK:#headreferee}}Head Referee{{/LINK}} directing a {{LINK:#team}}Team{{/LINK}} to Disable their {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}}:

a. <GG14> - Don’t destroy other {{LINK:#robot}}Robots{{/LINK}}
b. <GG17> - No {{LINK:#hold}}Holding{{/LINK}} for more than a 5-count
c. <SG7> - Don’t cross the {{LINK:#autonomousline}}Autonomous Line{{/LINK}}, and don’t interfere with your opponents’ actions. In the context of this rule, “excessive or egregious” refers to a {{LINK:#violation}}Violation{{/LINK}} or interaction that the {{LINK:#headreferee}}Head Referee{{/LINK}} has judged to be out of the {{LINK:#robot}}Robot’s{{/LINK}} control and/or is not showing any signs of improvement. Examples may include, but are not limited to:

• {{LINK:#hold}}Holding{{/LINK}} an opponent for 15+ seconds
• Repeated {{LINK:#violation}}Violations{{/LINK}} of <SG7> across multiple {{LINK:#match}}Matches{{/LINK}}

