generalDefinitions.definition:
{{BOLD}}Defensive{{/BOLD}} - A category of strategies, {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} actions, and/or {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} statuses that can be employed by a {{LINK:#team}}Team{{/LINK}} during a {{LINK:#match}}Match{{/LINK}}; see rules <GG14> and <GG15> for more information. A {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} is {{LINK:#defensive}}Defensive{{/LINK}} while it is engaged in actions that cannot increase its {{LINK:#alliance}}Alliance's{{/LINK}} score for the current {{LINK:#match}}Match{{/LINK}}, and instead limits an opponent’s ability to score or play the game. A {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} can be in possession of a scoring object and capable of scoring, but still be {{LINK:#defensive}}Defensive{{/LINK}} based on its actions. Examples include, but are not limited to:

• De-scoring in a way that doesn't increase points for the {{LINK:#robot}}Robot's{{/LINK}} own {{LINK:#alliance}}Alliance{{/LINK}}
• Limiting access to a portion of the {{LINK:#field}}Field{{/LINK}} while not attempting to score
• {{LINK:#hold}}Holding{{/LINK}}, blocking, impeding, or otherwise restricting or controlling an opponent’s movements
• {{LINK:#goalkeeping}}Goalkeeping{{/LINK}}
{{CALLOUT}}Remember, {{LINK:#defensive}}Defensive{{/LINK}} {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} actions or {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} statuses are not automatically {{LINK:#violation}}Violations{{/LINK}}. However, {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} actions or statuses that are performed or achieved in a {{LINK:#defensive}}Defensive{{/LINK}} manner are more likely to be {{LINK:#violation}}Violations{{/LINK}}, and {{LINK:#team}}Teams{{/LINK}} should be more careful when employing {{LINK:#defensive}}Defensive{{/LINK}} strategies. {{/CALLOUT}}

{{BOLD}}Offensive{{/BOLD}} - A category of strategies, {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} actions, and/or {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} statuses that can be employed by a {{LINK:#team}}Team{{/LINK}} during a {{LINK:#match}}Match{{/LINK}}; see rules <GG14> and <GG15> for more information. A {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} is {{LINK:#offensive}}Offensive{{/LINK}} while it is engaged in actions that could directly increase its {{LINK:#alliance}}Alliance's{{/LINK}} score for the current {{LINK:#match}}Match{{/LINK}}. Examples include, but are not limited to:

• Adding an object to a {{LINK:#goal}}Goal{{/LINK}} to score points
• Moving toward a {{LINK:#goal}}Goal{{/LINK}} with an object that could earn points for their {{LINK:#alliance}}Alliance{{/LINK}}
• Changing the status of a {{LINK:#fieldelement}}Field Element{{/LINK}} or scoring object that acts as a multiplier or scoring bonus for their {{LINK:#alliance}}Alliance{{/LINK}}
• Achieving (or attempting to achieve) any {{LINK:#robot}}Robot{{/LINK}} status that adds points to their {{LINK:#alliance}}Alliance's{{/LINK}} score
• Obtaining (or attempting to obtain) scoring objects
